ZH: 风烛残年，人生无常。
EN: In the twilight of life, nothing is permanent.

ZH: 风烛残年，岁月无情。
EN: In the waning years, time is merciless.

ZH: 风烛残年，事事皆不易。
EN: In the last stage of life, nothing is easy.

ZH: 风烛残年，梦想依旧。
EN: In the autumn of life, dreams still endure.

ZH: 风烛残年，岁月流逝。
EN: In the dwindling years, time marches on.

ZH: 风烛残年，别有一番滋味。
EN: In the twilight years, there is a unique flavor.

ZH: 风烛残年，人生无限。
EN: In the fading years, life is infinite.

ZH: 风烛残年，岁月如歌。
EN: In the late years, time sings.

ZH: 风烛残年，梦想未尽。
EN: In the remaining years, dreams are not yet fulfilled.

ZH: 风烛残年，执子之手，与子偕老。
EN: In the last years, holding hands and growing old together.

ZH: 风烛残年，岁月如梭。
EN: In the last stage of life, time flies.

ZH: 风烛残年，人生如戏。
EN: In the twilight of life, life is like a drama.

ZH: 风烛残年，不负岁月。
EN: In the waning years, do not disappoint the passing time.

ZH: 风烛残年，心如止水。
EN: In the dwindling years, the heart is calm.

ZH: 风烛残年，岁月无法回首。
EN: In the autumn of life, time cannot be turned back.

ZH: 风烛残年，梦想犹在。
EN: In the twilight years, dreams still exist.

ZH: 风烛残年，岁月匆匆。
EN: In the fading years, time rushes by.

ZH: 风烛残年，心境静好。
EN: In the remaining years, the mind is at peace.

ZH: 风烛残年，与子同眠。
EN: In the last years, sleeping together.
